The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 Ghana stun Korea 3-1

Berlin: Ivory Coast and Ghana each scored three goals and ended up with wins in World Cup warm-ups on Sunday. The Ivorians topped Slovenia 3-0, with Didier Drogba scoring twice, while Ghana beat 2002 semi-finalists South Korea 3-1. 

On Saturday, Switzerland, the Czech Republic and Portugal earned big wins. The Czechs got two goals from Jan Koller in a 3-0 win over Trinidad and Tobago, while Alexander Frei and Marco Streller scored two goals each to lead Switzerland over China 4-1. 

 Portugal beat Luxembourg via two goals from Simao Sabrosa and one from Luis Figo. Poland beat Croatia 1-0 with Euzebiusz Smolarek heading in. 

 Later, Spain beat Egypt 2-0 as Raul Gonzalez ended a seven-month goal drought, striking from close range in the 14th minute at Martinez Valero Stadium. Substitute Jose Antonio Reyes added the second. 

In another match, Peter Crouch scored a hattrick in Englands 6-0 win over Jamaica. 

 (AP) 




